About third party service providers
Google Analytics: IP addresses are anonymized. No Personal Information is processed or stored
Hotjar: keystrokes are not being recorded. No Personal Information is processed or/and stored.
Gmail for Business, Stripe, Intercom: Personal Information processed or/and stored in accordance with EU General Data Protection Regulation (EU-GDPR)
Users content
When creating an interactive map using the Mapme service, you will typically enter and upload information such as addresses, text descriptions, photos, and videos which constitute the “Users Content”.
Mapme will collect and process the “Users content”. For such purposes, Mapme shall be considered as a “Processor” and not as the “Controller” (as defined in the European Union General Data Protection Regulation) of such Users-of-Users Information. The Users shall be considered as the “Controllers” of the “Users Content” and are responsible for complying with all laws and regulations that may apply to the collection and control of such information, including all privacy and data protection laws of all relevant jurisdictions.
If you decide to publish the map and share it (social network, website embeds…) this information becomes available to the public.
You can decide at any moment to delete your User Content by using the “Delete” option in the Mapme dashboard. However, even after its deletion, copies of User Content may remain viewable in the online cache and archived pages or if any Users-of-Users have copied or stored such User Content.
So, please do not include information on your map if you don’t want it to become publicly available. You do so at your own risk.
Data Hosting and service providers
‘Mapme Users’ personal Information is maintained, processed, and stored by Mapme and our authorized affiliates in the United States of America using secured cloud storage from Amazon AWS.
Mapme has signed the AWS Data Processing Addendum which gives Mapme customers the assurance that AWS will give customers’ data the same high levels of security, privacy, and data protection that it would receive in the EU.
Law Enforcement, Legal Requests, and Duties
Where permitted by local data protection laws, Mapme may disclose or otherwise allow others access to your Personal Information pursuant to a legal request, such as a subpoena, legal proceedings, search warrant, or court order, or in compliance with applicable laws, if we have good faith belief that the law requires us to do so, with or without notice to you.
Mapme may share your Personal Information with others if we believe in good faith that this will help protect the rights, property or personal safety of Mapme, any of our Users, any Users-of-Users, or any member of the general public, with or without notice to you.
We will not sell your personally identifiable information to any company or organization except we may transfer your personally identifiable information to a successor entity upon a merger, consolidation, or other corporate reorganization in which Mapme participates or to a purchaser of all or substantially all assets of Map Labs ltd. to which this Site relates.
Single Sign-On, Social Media Features, and Framed Pages
Our Services include Social Media features such as “Social sharing” and single sign-on features, such as “Facebook Connect”. The use of those features may collect information such as your IP address and may set a cookie to enable them to function properly. Your interactions with these third parties features are governed by their policies and not ours.
In addition, our users may integrate Third Party Services or other parties’ content via page framing techniques (iframes) for example using the “Integrated Media” feature. The use of those features may also collect information such as your IP address and may set a cookie to enable them to function properly. Please be aware that if you choose to interact or share any Personal Information via such Frames, you are in fact providing it to these third parties and not to us, and such interactions and sharing too are governed by such third parties’ policies and not ours.
Communications from Mapme
We may use your Personal Information to send you product updates and offers by e-mail, or direct messages if you are a user login in to the Mapme service.
We will never share your personal data with any third party for marketing purposes.
If you do not wish to receive those messages, you may notify Mapme at any time or follow the “unsubscribe” in the communications you receive.
Mapme may also contact you with important information regarding our Services, or your use thereof. For example, we may send you a notice (through any of the means available to us) if a Mapme service is temporarily suspended for maintenance; reply to your support ticket or e-mail; send you reminders or warnings regarding upcoming or late payments for your current or upcoming subscriptions; forward abuse complaints regarding your Map; or notify you of material changes in our Services.
It is important that you are always able to receive such messages. For this reason, Users are not able to opt out of receiving such Service and Billing Messages unless they are no longer a Mapme Users.
Correction, Updating, and Deleting of your Personally Identifiable Information
You have control over your Personal Information. You can request a copy of, update, delete, or limit the use of the Personal Information you have stored with us. Just send us a request using
our contact form
. We will respond to your request within a timeframe imposed by local laws or a reasonable timeframe.
Some of the information may also be corrected and/ or, updated through your account.
If you are a User and wish to permanently delete your Mapme account, we will erase all of your information from Mapme’s databases. After completing this process, your account and all its data will be removed permanently, and Mapme will not be able to restore your account or retrieve your data in the future.
Data Retention
We may continue to retain Personal Information such as for example Invoices and Receipts even after you deactivate your User Account and/or cease to use the Mapme service, as reasonably necessary to comply with our legal obligations, to resolve disputes regarding our Users or their Users-of-Users, prevent fraud and abuse, enforce our agreements and/or protect our legitimate interests.
Where your Personal Information is no longer required we will ensure it is securely deleted.
Privacy Policy Updates
Due to the Internet’s rapidly evolving nature, Mapme may need to update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If so, Mapme will post its updated Privacy Policy on our Site located at https://Mapme.com so you are always aware of what personally identifiable information we may collect and how we may use this information. Mapme encourages you to review this Privacy Policy regularly for any changes. Your continued use of this Site and/or continued provision of personally identifiable information to us will be subject to the terms of the then-current Privacy Policy.
Children’s Privacy
Mapme recognizes the privacy interests of children and minors under the age of 18 and we encourage parents and guardians to take an active role in their children’s online activities and interests. This Site is not intended for children and minors under the age of 18. Mapme does not target its Services or this Site to children and minors under the age of 18. Mapme does not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children and minors under the age of 18.
Cookies
We may use small text files called cookies to improve the overall user experience. Cookies do not permit us to personally identify you. You may opt out through your browser settings or other sources – but please note that this may adversely affect the way you experience our services.
Security
We may employ procedural and technological security measures that are reasonably designed to help protect your personally identifiable information from loss, unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. Mapme may use encryption, password protection, and other security measures to help prevent unauthorized access to your personally identifiable information. The data that you transmit as part of your use of the Services (“Storage Data”) is in encrypted form and Mapme does not have access to your Storage Data in its unencrypted form.
Contact Us
If you have any questions regarding this Privacy Policy please contact us via
our contact form.
